A bag contains 10 Red Candy and 10 Blue Candy. 
Pick two Candies randomly from the bag.

If two blue Candies are drawn then put them both back to bag

If two Red Candies are drawn then keep them out from bag

if one Red Candy and one Blue Candy then put Red Candy back to bag 
and keep the Blue candy out from bag

Create a simulation and run the simulation 100 times, based on this run.

Estimate likelihood percentage of the last candy in the bag
Estimate likelihood percentage of the last candy being blue in the bag
Estimate likelihood percentage of the last candy being Red in the bag
